<dl id="un3006m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un3" href="#un3006">UN3: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un3all.htm#un3006m"> (VIII.A.5) 6(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &ldquo;Australian&rdquo; Greeks in / Ithaka = old &ldquo;Egyptians&rsquo; / in old &ldquo;megara&rdquo; real Egypt fakes / today French novels. <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un3006m"> <li>Ulysses unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Inutile de dire que, rentr&eacute;s au pays, ces &laquo;Australiens&raquo; &mdash; au temps d&apos;Ulysse, Ithaque avait des &laquo;&Eacute;gyptiens&raquo;, &mdash; gr&acirc;ce &agrave; leur fortune et &agrave; leurs illustres aventures, jouissent d&apos;une l&eacute;gitime popularit&eacute;. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> C&apos;est &agrave; eux que Port Vathy doit sa propret&eacute;, ses maisons confortables, sa salle de lecture, o&ugrave; les Ithaciens d&apos;aujourd&apos;hui viennent lire surtout les romans fran&ccedil;ais &mdash; au temps d&apos;Ulysse, dans leurs megara, ils s&apos;int&eacute;ressaient aux contes d&apos;&Egrave;gypte. <br><font color="green">[Needless to say, on returning home, these &lsquo;Australians&rsquo; ?</font>#<font color="green">[80]</font>#<font color="green">[93]</font> in Ulysses&apos;s time Ithaca had &lsquo;Egyptians&rsquo; &mdash; thanks to their fortune and their illustrious adventures, enjoy legitimate popularity. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> It is to them that Vathy owes its cleanliness, its comfortable houses, its reading room, where the Ithacans of today come to read French novels mainly &mdash; in the time of Ulysses, in their palaces, they took an interest in tales of Egypt.] <small> Victor B&eacute;rard, <a name="VBLP2" href="/udra/udex.htm#vblp2"><cite title="source">Les Ph&eacute;niciens et l'Odyss&eacute;e</cite></a> (1902), II, 527</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="s16018c" href="s16all.htm#s16018c">Sheet 16.018(c)</a>.</mm> </dd></dl>
